{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 190°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper.","Place sugar in mixing bowl and pulverise <nobr>30 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add apricots, chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Rinse mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg white, salt and honey in mixing bowl and whisk until stiff <nobr>2 min\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong> ","Add almond and apricot mixture, nuts and 150 g icing sugar and stir <nobr>20 sec\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","With wet hands, shape 24 little balls (Ø approx. 3 cm), roll in remaining icing sugar and place on baking tray approx. 1 cm apart. Let the amaretti rest for 10-15 minutes to let the surface dry. Bake for 6-10 minutes (190°C), allow to cool and store cool and dry in jars."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["220 g sugar","180 g almonds","100 g dried apricots, pitted","2 egg whites","1 pinch salt","2 tsp honey","100 g mixed nuts, whole (e.g. pistachios, almonds and hazelnuts)"]}],"id":"r126690","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-scRz-Yoiu90\/XZWpvhUMwxI\/AAAAAAAAfOY\/rDUBR_CECkYAA8-Kn9HRE9e4xAc6c7kVwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4pXLwhSLgPVoAP3z.png","title":"Apricot amaretti","publishedAt":"2017-08-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"12 g","calories":"515 kJ \/ 123 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, bowl, oven","basicInfo":["medium","15m","40m","24 pieces"]}